    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Decanter wagons in the shape of a naval jolly boat resting on four wheels or small rollers and having two large circular recesses for decanters and sometimes two smaller recesses for stoppers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000021291/Newman, Illustrated Dictionary of Silverware (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Carros para licores con la forma de un pequeño bote naval montados en cuatro ruedas o pequeñas ruedecitas y con dos grandes compartimentos circulares para botellas de licor y algunas veces dos compartimentos más pequeños para tapones. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Decanteerfleswagentjes in de vorm van een marinejol, rustend op vier wielen of kleine rollers, met twee grote ronde uitsparingen voor decanteerflessen en soms twee kleinere uitsparingen voor de stoppen. Geen Nederlands equivalent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>海軍單座艇造型的酒瓶車，下方裝設四個輪子或小型滾輪，具有兩個大的圓形酒瓶置放凹槽，有些會另設兩個小凹槽放置瓶塞。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
